Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom, of Benue State has described the outgone year, 2021 as tough one for the entire nation. The Governor spoke on Friday during crossover night Wonders Mega Parish, Redeemed Christian Church of God, RCCG, Gboko road Makurdi the state capital. Ortom crossed over to 2022 in the church with his wife, Dr Eunice Ortom and family members. The governor, who prayed for a better 2022, admitted that the past year was terrible for Nigerian leaders. He thanked Benue people for their resilience, understanding and prayers for him and his administration and encouraged Nigerians not to loose hope but trust in God for a better country.